      <details>
        <summary>What are the best growth stocks to buy now in May 2025?</summary>
        <p>The top growth stocks generally include high-performing technology and consumer cyclical companies that demonstrate strong historical and projected earnings growth, though specific rankings depend on current market valuations and sector trends.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do you identify the best stocks to buy now?</summary>
        <p>Identifying the best stocks involves analyzing a combination of qualitative factors like competitive advantage and management quality, alongside quantitative metrics like revenue growth, P/E ratio, and free cash flow.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Are growth stocks better than dividend stocks?</summary>
        <p>Neither is inherently better; growth stocks offer higher capital appreciation potential but more volatility, while dividend stocks provide steady income and lower volatility. The choice depends on an investor's goals and risk tolerance.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is a good P/E ratio for a growth stock?</summary>
        <p>A 'good' P/E ratio is highly relative to the company's sector and growth rate. Growth stocks typically command higher P/E ratios than the broader market, often ranging from 25 to over 50, reflecting expectations of rapid future expansion.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What are the risks of investing in growth stocks?</summary>
        <p>Growth stocks are highly sensitive to changes in interest rates and market sentiment. Because their valuations are based on future expectations, any miss in earnings or slowing of growth can lead to significant price declines.</p>
      </details>
